      "section3": "3. Key Highlights",
      "highlight1Title": "Depreciation Surge from EUV Equipment",
      "highlight1Text": "New EUV lithography equipment in front-end processes increased depreciation by <strong>+28.5B KRW</strong> vs previous month. This accounts for <strong>{{pct}}%</strong> of the total increase and is the largest cost driver. Annual depreciation per EUV tool is approximately 200B KRW, with continued pressure expected from additional deployments.",
      "highlight2Title": "Key Material Price Increases (CMP Slurry)",
      "highlight2Text": "Material costs rose by <strong>+16.2B KRW</strong>, driven by CMP slurry (+3.5B), photoresist (+2.8B), and etching gas (+1.2B) price increases. Global supply chain issues and rising demand for high-purity materials are the underlying causes.",
      "highlight3Title": "Test Process Automation Benefits Realized",
      "highlight3Text": "Automation in test processes achieved labor cost savings (<strong>-4.0B KRW</strong>) and test board efficiency gains (<strong>-1.0B KRW</strong>), totaling <strong>-5.2B KRW</strong> in cost reduction. This demonstrates positive ROI from company-wide automation investment.",
      "highlight4Title": "Continued HBM Product Cost Escalation",
      "highlight4Text": "HBM products have shown 6 consecutive months of cost increases (Aug 480B → Jan 585B, <strong>+21.9%</strong>). Surging AI server HBM demand, production expansion, and increasing complexity of high-stack processes are driving costs upward.",
